a car bomb exploded next to a syrian army 
checkpoint in moslem west beirut on sunday morning wounding at 
least 15 people police said 
police said a syrian soldier at the checkpoint was among the 
casualties most of the other wounded were lebanese civilians 
including women and children 
a creamcolored mercedes packed with 88 pounds of tnt blew up at 
840 am 140 am edt only two yards from the checkpoint 
opposite a restaurant in the seaside raouche district police 
reported 
at least eight cars parked nearby were destroyed 
police said the car had been parked saturday evening near the 
restaurant which perches atop a cliff overlooking the 
mediterranean they could not determine who owned the mercedes 
syrian troops armed with rocketpropelled grenades and 
automatic rifles sealed off the blast scene 
red cross ambulances evacuated the casualties as the syrians 
fired in the air to make way for them 
