chavez a vegetarian began the fast in good health and remained 
mentally sharp throughout 
the mass was chavezs first public appearance since aug 11 
when he ceased attending nightly community meetings 
chavez began this fast to emphasize his demand for a ban on five 
pesticides used on table grapes the union claims the materials 
cause cancer in field workers and pose other serious health risks 
grape growers and grocers blasted chavez and the union for 
unduly frightening consumers about the safety of table grapes in an 
effort to fight a political battle 
chavez raised the pesticide issue in 1986 and called for 
captan dinoseb phosdrin methyl bromide and parathion to be taken 
off the market 
in the early days of this fast chavez held union meetings 
visited with union delegations meditated prayed and went on a 
daily walk 
as his strength waned chavez steadily scaled back his 
activities he spent increasing amounts of time bedridden in a 
small bare room in the unions retirement village and his staff 
entered the room only at his request 
