armtek corp which has rejected a 550 
million buyout offer from mark iv industries inc says it is 
negotiating with a third party interested in buying the plastics 
and chemicals company 
the announcement friday came one day after mark iv sweetened its 
offer for all of armteks stock to 44 a share from its original 
40ashare bid 
armteks board which rejected mark ivs original share as 
inadequate has not responded to the latest offer 
the company said it informed the securities and exchange 
commission that negotiations with the third party may be 
dependent upon future actions of mark iv industries with respect to 
the amended offer 
armtek earlier said it would consider a thirdparty acquisition 
and in its sec filing the company said it was also considering 
recapitalization proposals 
investors apparently expect bidding for armtek to continue the 
companys stock rose 1 a share to 4650 in new york stock 
exchange trading friday 
armtek is facing four class action suits in delaware where it 
is incorporated from shareholders who charge the companys 
directors are trying to thwart the mark iv takeover attempt and 
havent satisfactorily explored the offer 
one suit claims armteks directors have embarked upon a course 
of action designed to entrench themselves in the management and 
control of armtek and to protect and enhance their personal 
financial benefits at the expense of shareholders 
armtek formerly known as armstrong rubber co is a supplier of 
engineered drive and heat exchange systems modules and components 
and specialty polymers it had 12 billion in sales last year 
two month ago armtek sold its largest unit armstrong tire co 
to the italian tire maker pirelli group for 197 million capping a 
corporate restructuring 
mark iv based in west amherst ny produces professional 
audio technical and aerospace products the company had 1987 sales 
of 292 million 
